commit.message:
Convert TimeZoneField string value to timezone object on assignment

Add a descriptor_class that deserializes a string
TimeZoneField value to a timezone object (pytz timezone
or zoneinfo depending on settings) when it is assigned.

As a side effect, invalid (non-blank) timezone names are
detected immediately (rather than at save/full_clean time),
and will immediately raise a ValidationError.

Closes #57

commit.message:
backends/zoneinfo.py: Skip using the "Factory" timezone

Referencing the "Factory" timezone can lead to ValueError exceptions on some systems, e.g. FreeBSD, if the system zoneinfo database is used:

ValueError: Invalid STD format in b'<Local time zone must be set--use tzsetup>0'

Thus drop the "Factory" timezone from the sets before iterating over them to avoid the aforementioned issue.

tree 82571eaa2c2ea8a6e840b2ff4a0be626f743479c

backends/zoneinfo.py: Skip using the "Factory" timezone

Referencing the "Factory" timezone can lead to ValueError exceptions on some systems, e.g. FreeBSD, if the system zoneinfo database is used:

ValueError: Invalid STD format in b'<Local time zone must be set--use tzsetup>0'

Thus drop the "Factory" timezone from the sets before iterating over them to avoid the aforementioned issue.

commit.message:
Use zoneinfo.available_timezones() (#108)

* USE_PYTZ as env var in tests

* Remove pytz from dependencies

It still shows up in dev env because django-rest-framework requires it

* Switch to TZ_ENGINE env var for tests

* Consolidate pytz/zoneinfo logic in compat

Also, switch the default choices over to use zoneinfo.available_timezones()
when running with use_ptyz=False

* Clean up some stray direct pytz/zoneinfo references

* Move the default use_pytz into compat.py

* Clean up some more stray 'import pytz'

* Get pytz imports out of the tests

* Remove unused imports

* Cleanup more direct use of pytz

* Only run serializer field test when pytz present

* A few more fixes

* Fix typo in CI/CD

* Timezone engine "backends"

* Support some fields with use_pytz=true, others false

* README updates

* Update docstring, comments
